        <abstract>
            <p>Sad about Oliver’s loss.</p> 
<p>JDH’s reference to odd <hi rend="italic">Begonia</hi> at same time as an article about it came out in <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi> [(1866): 313–14].</p> 
            <p>Is astonished that Pangenesis seems perplexing to JDH. Pleads guilty to its being "wildly abominably speculative (worthy even of Herbert Spencer)".</p>
